fr:mainmatter.html:p:
For examples:


The rule instance with the single premise-argument p \;/\; q and the conclusion-argument p \land  q \;/\; r is written as:


\usepackage {ebproof}
\begin {prooftree}
\hypo {p \;/\; q}
\infer 1[]{p \land  q \;/\; r}
\end {prooftree}



The rule instance with the two premise-arguments p \;/\; p and p \;/\; q and the conclusion-argument p, q \;/\; p is written as:


\usepackage {ebproof}
\begin {prooftree}
\hypo {p \;/\; p}
\hypo {p \;/\; q}
\infer 2[]{p, q \;/\; p}
\end {prooftree}



The rule instance with the empty set of premise-arguments and the conclusion-argument q \rightarrow  r \;/\; s is written as:


\usepackage {ebproof}
\begin {prooftree}
\hypo {}
\infer 1[]{q \rightarrow  r \;/\; s}
\end {prooftree}

